79
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:11,040
This is what Ms Wang told me.

80
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:13,240
Do you need to dress like this
for a parent-teacher conference?

81
00:07:13,330 --> 00:07:14,210
Take your hands off.

82
00:07:14,420 --> 00:07:15,250
Whose clothes is this?

83
00:07:15,330 --> 00:07:16,370
Where does the designer bag come from?

84
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:17,770
I'm warning you

85
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:19,450
not to mess with it. It's expensive.

86
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:21,160
Go home quickly.

87
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:22,530
Go to dinner by yourself.

88
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:26,960
What do you want again?

89
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,570
I warn you.

90
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:30,290
Don't talk nonsense.

91
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:31,330
Don't brag.

92
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:32,970
If you can't do that, go back now.

93
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:33,890
No need for the parent-teacher conference.

94
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:36,290
Leave me alone.

95
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:38,210
I will say whatever I want to say.

96
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,690
When I spoke at the conference,

97
00:07:40,780 --> 00:07:43,240
there was no you.

98
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:45,570
Li Qing Tong.

99
00:07:45,659 --> 00:07:47,930
You didn't used to have
parent-teacher conferences either.

100
00:07:48,650 --> 00:07:50,930
Li Jin Bu, don't go too far.

101
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:53,530
Other children don't call
their mothers by their names.

102
00:07:54,370 --> 00:07:55,590
Go home now.

103
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:56,560
One.

104
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:59,590
Two.

105
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,740
[High School Department]

106
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:12,200
As the old saying goes,

107
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:13,250
"touch pitch and you will be defiled."

108
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,850
[Welcome, parents]

109
00:08:14,850 --> 00:08:16,610
Li Jin Bu's current achievements

110
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:18,170
and my own cultural level

111
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:20,120
are completely inseparable.

112
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:21,700
Talented people

113
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:24,450
often come from scholarly families.

114
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:25,810
From my father onwards,

115
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:27,810
our family has always

116
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,890
been an intellectual family.

117
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:31,650
We strive to cultivate a family
atmosphere for our children

118
00:08:31,740 --> 00:08:35,200
that loves learning and knowledge.

119
00:08:35,289 --> 00:08:37,600
As stated in the motto of my alma mater,

120
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:39,890
"rich in knowledge and
tenacious in propose."

121
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:41,539
What on earth

122
00:08:41,820 --> 00:08:43,049
is "tenacious in propose?"

123
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:44,169
It should be "tenacious in purpose."

124
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:45,730
Rich in knowledge and
tenacious in purpose.

125
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:47,960
My child is

126
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:49,530
smart,

127
00:08:49,610 --> 00:08:51,090
studious

128
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:52,800
and good-looking.

129
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,410
This can be said to be
completely inherited from

130
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:57,760
all my personal good genes.

131
00:08:57,850 --> 00:08:58,730
Thank you all.

132
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:00,610
What a bragger.

133
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,530
May I ask

134
00:09:02,810 --> 00:09:04,050
which is your alma mater?

135
00:09:04,130 --> 00:09:05,320
Fudan University.

136
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,760
I am also from Fudan University.

137
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:09,370
Rich in knowledge and
tenacious of purpose.

138
00:09:10,170 --> 00:09:11,250
Which class are you from?

139
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,570
What a coincidence.

140
00:09:13,660 --> 00:09:14,770
And

141
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:15,880
what class are you from?

142
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:16,890
The class of 2001.

143
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:17,850
I'm from the class of 2002.

144
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:18,850
We're not the same.

145
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:21,960
And what is your major?

146
00:09:23,050 --> 00:09:23,970
Chinese language.

147
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:25,020
Chinese language?

148
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:27,090
Is there a girl named
Wang Xiao Yu in your class?

149
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:31,280
Yes.

150
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:32,330
What a coincidence.

151
00:09:32,410 --> 00:09:34,010
I'm in an office with Ms Wang.

152
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:34,930
After the meeting,

153
00:09:35,020 --> 00:09:36,290
we can get together.

154
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:38,410
It's okay, Ms Wang.

155
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,570
This gathering does not matter.

156
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:42,330
After all, so many years have passed

157
00:09:42,660 --> 00:09:45,170
that we may not know each other
when we see each other again.

158
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,010
Right?

159
00:09:46,100 --> 00:09:48,530
It doesn't matter which
university you come from.

160
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:50,290
What matters is the learning itself.

161
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,530
Does it mean

162
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:53,760
that you deserve to have a good life

163
00:09:53,850 --> 00:09:55,490
only if you go to a
prestigious university?

164
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:57,040
Of course not.

165
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,810
I have to leave now.

166
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,800
I wish you all a happy life
and more and more money.

167
00:10:00,890 --> 00:10:01,770
Goodbye.

168
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:03,050
Thank you. Bye.

169
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:05,640
Thank you, Ms Wang.

170
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:11,300
Let's go home.

171
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:13,010
Did I say

172
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,170
don't brag?

173
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:15,530
Can you be a little smarter when you lie?

174
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:16,610
I didn't lie.

175
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,690
I applied for Fudan
and just didn't get in.

176
00:10:18,780 --> 00:10:20,730
So I regard it as my alma mater,

177
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:21,690
can't I?

178
00:10:22,060 --> 00:10:23,730
Is it up to you to decide your alma mater?

179
00:10:23,820 --> 00:10:25,210
Did you ever go to university?

180
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:27,720
Who do you mean?

181
00:10:28,660 --> 00:10:29,650
Since you went to university,

182
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:30,410
where is your diploma?

183
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:31,370
Show it to me.

184
00:10:32,060 --> 00:10:34,050
Enough.

185
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,530
Your teacher just asked
me about university.

186
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:36,650
You asked for my diploma.

187
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:39,080
Do you want me to make a fool of myself?

188
00:10:40,020 --> 00:10:40,900
Stand there.

189
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,480
Don't mean mug me.

190
00:10:43,860 --> 00:10:44,800
I didn't pay so much for you

191
00:10:44,890 --> 00:10:46,340
to go to such a good school

192
00:10:46,430 --> 00:10:48,170
so that you can scold me all day.

193
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:49,090
Okay.

194
00:10:49,180 --> 00:10:50,050
Tuition is expensive.

195
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:51,170
I will drop out, OK?

196
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:52,450
I don't want to be a burden to you.

197
00:10:54,490 --> 00:10:55,730
I don't care a lick.

198
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:40,050
Li Qing Tong.

199
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:41,560
You didn't pay the electricity bill again.

200
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:45,050
[Li Qing Tong]

201
00:11:48,370 --> 00:11:48,490
[Baby]

202
00:11:48,490 --> 00:11:49,370
Cheers!

203
00:11:54,010 --> 00:11:54,890
Mr Xu,

204
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,050
I tell you,

205
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:58,570
